Generate a boilerplate for-each block:
parent = hou.node('/obj/geo1')
begin = parent.createNode('block_begin')
end = parent.createNode('block_end')
end.parm('itermethod').set(1) # Pieces
end.setInput(0, begin)

Print nodes that failed to cook:
for n in hou.node('/').allSubChildren():
    if n.errors():
        print(f'{n.path()}: {n.errors()}')

Helpful for cleaning up a mess:
for n in hou.node('/obj/geo1').children():
    n.setSelectableInViewport(True)

Purge a container node:
for n in hou.node('/obj/geo1').children():
    n.destroy()

Check if a node has enough inputs linked:
if len(hou.node('/obj/geo1/merge1').inputs()) < 1:
    print('Warning: Merge has no inputs')

Mute/ghost selected nodes:
for n in hou.selectedNodes():
    n.setGenericFlag(hou.nodeFlag.Display, False)

